Here's a question that is as such: Examine each of these chemical equations to determine which equation is correctly balanced.
The only answers which are applicable are these:
A) Mg(NO_{3})_{2} + K_{2}CO_{3} -> MgCO_{3} + KNO_{3}
B) Mg(NO_{3})_{2} + K_{2}CO_{3} -> MgCO_{3} + 2KNO_{3}
C) 2Mg(NO_{3})_{2} + K_{2}CO_{3} -> 2MgCO_{3} + KNO_{3}
D) Mg(NO_{3})_{2} + 2K_{2}CO_{3} -> MgCO_{3} + 2KNO_{3}
What is the most likely answer to this question?

Which of the following represents the process of photosynthesis?
A: 6CO_{2} + 6H_{2}O -> C_{6}H_{12}O_{6} +6O_{2}
B: C_{6}H_{12}O_{6} -> 6CO_{2} + 6H_{2}O
C: 2H_{2} + O_{2} -> 2H_{2}O
D: 2H_{2}O -> 2H_{2} + O_{2}
